{
  "texts": [
    "There can be delays in message delivery which can delay the data adaptation process with the correct size.",
    "Such delays can then lead to a mismatch between the data size and the DNN size on the server, subsequently impacting the application performance.",
    "However, we anticipate that these delays will be considered when estimating the bandwidth, and therefore the Jellyfish scheduler will handle such conditions in the next scheduling round.",
    "Additionally, we piggyback the metadata (e.g., data/input size) on every response to the client.",
    "As a result, clients can recover from unreliable conditions as soon as the connection stabilizes."
  ]
}